  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" The State of Chattisgarh versus Ashok Bhoi Etc. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_2_1785_1789','2025INSC256'); ><font size='4'> <strong>THE STATE OF CHATTISGARH<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>ASHOK BHOI ETC. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 2 S.C.R. 1785</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 256</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010003522025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : BELA M. TRIVEDI, PRASANNA BHALACHANDRA VARALE</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the High Court was justified in allowing the criminal appeal preferred by accused-respondent and dismissing acquittal appeal preferred by the State, thereby acquitting both the accused persons. Headnotes&dagger; Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 &ndash; Whether the chain of circumstances to prove the guilt of the accused persons as the case is based on Circumstantial Evidence &ndash; Correctness: Held: The entire case of the prosecution hinged on the circumstantial evidence, there was no eye-witness to the alleged incident &ndash; So far as accused-AB is<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 27-02-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 1258/2015</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_2_1785_1789','2025INSC256','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','